Nigerians are about to have a real-time experience with Jack Dorsey, Twitter’s CEO as he prepares for his trip to Nigeria. Jack who announced this on Twitter, one of Nigeria’s favourite social media platform, also stated some countries he would be visiting in the African continent this November. The other countries listed are Ethiopia, Ghana, and South Africa. He tweeted this on his page while stating that in each of these countries, he will be meeting with local entrepreneurs.  According to the Global State of Digital, Nigerians spend an average of 3 hours 17 minutes on social media, more than the global average of 3 hours, 14 minutes. In anticipation of his coming, Nigerians have taken to the platform to express their concerns: 